## Your job

For each keyword item where vault-match produced a hit
(``match != null``), read the existing vault page in full
(frontmatter + body) and write a **merged item** whose
``definition`` integrates the existing page's content with the new
info this run extracted. Coherent prose, not "also: …" appendage.

You MUST:

- **Preserve** every fact the existing page asserts unless this
  run's source contradicts it. If a contradiction exists, surface
  it in ``rationale`` and prefer the existing page's claim (the
  user has already vetted it).
- Produce a ``rationale`` (1-3 sentences) describing what new info
  this run contributes. If none, set ``new_info_present: false``
  and say so plainly in ``rationale`` ("This run repeats the
  existing definition; merge keeps the page as-is.").
- Produce an ``existing_summary`` (1 line) describing what the
  existing page said before merging. The operator reads this to
  decide whether the rewrite is worth applying.
- **Not** introduce new prose unrelated to the keyword's meaning.
  Stay scoped to the term's definition.
- Mark ``merged_item.definition_source: merged`` to flag the
  hybrid provenance. Place this run's source quote in
  ``merged_item.source_quote`` even when the existing page also
  cited a quote — the existing citation lives in the page text
  the agent read.

If the existing page is empty, corrupt, or its definition is
unrelated to this term (different sense), set
``new_info_present: true`` and produce a ``merged_item`` that
equals this run's extracted item verbatim, with a rationale
explaining the disagreement.

